Colombian Stocks: Canacol Energy, Exito, Interconexion Electrica

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-08-02T20:33:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/colombian-stocks-canacol-energy-exito-interconexion-electrica.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 1 percent to 13,957.98 while the Colcap
Index fell 0.6 percent to 1,658.98  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  , Colombiaâ€™s largest retailer,
rose 0.2 percent to 24,100 pesos. The company plans to use part
of a planned share sale of as much as $1.4 billion to fund
construction of new malls, Chief Executive Officer Gonzalo
Restrepo told La Republica newspaper yesterday.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Toronto-based  oil
company  with fields in Colombia, fell 1.3 percent to 1,890
pesos. Oil dropped for a third day in New York, the longest
losing streak since May.  Interconexion Electrica SA (ISA)  , a Colombian
electricity and roadway company, fell 0.7 percent to 12,180
pesos. The company said second-quarter net income declined to
79.8 billion pesos ($45.2 million), from 95.8 billion pesos a
year ago, according to a regulatory filing yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
